</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Plans for this library</strong>\n\nAs time permits in the next few weeks, I hope to have this complete package cleaned up and ready to use. Here\'s what else have been developed and is in the process of being cleaned up:\n<ul>\n	<li>MATLAB and R libraries</li>\n	<li>A fast, optimized console application for importing delimited data from text files. This program also can filter text files (so you can split up a file containing different tickers into separate time series).</li>\n	<li>A console application to dump subsets of time series to text files</li>\n	<li>A GUI application that lets you make charts of your time series in view the raw data as tables</li>\n	<li>An example of how to write a C++ program to aggregate raw timeseries data to lower frequencies (minute or second data from millisecond data).</li>\n</ul>\n<h2></h2>','Time Series Database','','inherit','open','open','','53-autosave','','','2012-07-09 10:12:00','2012-07-09 14:12:00','',53,'http://andyfiedler.com/blog/53-autosave-59/',0,'revision','',0),(60,1,'2012-06-23 12:03:10','2012-06-23 16:03:10','<h2>Motivation</h2>\r\n&nbsp;','Time Series Database','','inherit','open','open','','53-revision-3','','','2012-06-23 12:03:10','2012-06-23 16:03:10','',53,'http://andyfiedler.com/blog/53-revision-3-60/',0,'revision','',0),(61,1,'2012-06-23 12:27:58','2012-06-23 16:27:58','<h2>Overview</h2>\r\nThis project was started as a way to organize massive amounts of time series data. We had terabytes of high frequency foreign exchange data and wanted to run models on it in common statistical programming languages like R and MATLAB. However, with that much data, there is no way we could fit it into memory on a normal desktop PC.\r\n\r\nBelieve it or not, there is no simple, affordable solution to this problem out there. We tried stuffing it into MySQL (epic fail), SAS (couldn\'t figure out a good way to index it, plus we wanted to use MATLAB and R for analysis), and flat text files (sort of wor